Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. 12:20 PM Defendant Gary Gorman Tainter Jr not in court.  Attorney Stephanie E Thomas-Schmidt in court for Gary Gorman Tainter Jr.  Attorney Jennifer Gross in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case and recites appearances. State requests warrant for Sawyer and surrounding counties. DEF Atty notes that he was present in courtroom but left, requests for warrant to be stayed. State has no objection. Court stays warrant until Friday, 9/2/22 at 11am for possible voluntary appearance.

State begins examination.   11:43 AM  Witness identified the DEF, court indicates the record will reflect.  State continues examination.   11:46 AM  Cross-Examination by Attorney Otten.  11:48 AM Attny Otten no further questions.  11:48 AM  State re-direct.  11:49 AM  Attny Otten re-cross.
